{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/how-is-cost-of-delay-in-safe-calculated/","result":{"data":{"post":{"id":"cG9zdDo1OTUx","excerpt":"<p>TL;DR: Poorly. Not recommended! If you want to delve into the details, read this. (The main problems are that it uses some made up relative terms and then combines them &#8230; </p>\n<div><a href=\"/how-is-cost-of-delay-in-safe-calculated/\" class=\"more-link\">Read More</a></div>\n","content":"\n<p>TL;DR: Poorly. Not recommended!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to delve into the details, read <a href=\"http://blackswanfarming.com/safe-and-weighted-shortest-job-first-wsjf/\">this</a>. (The main problems are that it uses some made up relative terms and then combines them in a way that is illogical.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;ve already started using the made up relative terms that SAFe suggests, all is not lost. At least make sure you combine them in <a href=\"http://blackswanfarming.com/safes-cost-of-delay-a-suggested-improvement/\">a more sensible way</a>. (That should avoid the worst of the nonsense results.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If Value =0, or urgency = 0, then of course, the Cost of Delay should be zero. If it&#8217;s not, you can be pretty sure you&#8217;ve combined your made-up terms in a way that doesn&#8217;t make sense. Might want to fix that!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2><strong>Cost of Delay = Value x Urgency</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you haven&#8217;t started, and you&#8217;re <a href=\"http://blackswanfarming.com/why-are-people-afraid-of-estimating-value/\">afraid of quantifying</a> Cost of Delay, then you could <a href=\"http://blackswanfarming.com/qualitative-cost-delay/\">try this qualitative approach</a> â€“ at least to do a quick scan of options. If you&#8217;re feeling brave, you could then have a go at quantifying the Cost of Delay for a few options that you think are  the highest value and urgency.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"695\" height=\"419\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_695,h_419/v1613032063/W/cost-of-delay-the-vital-few/cost-of-delay-the-vital-few.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4101\" srcset=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/v1613032063/W/cost-of-delay-the-vital-few/cost-of-delay-the-vital-few.png 695w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_300,h_181,c_scale/v1613032063/W/cost-of-delay-the-vital-few/cost-of-delay-the-vital-few-300x181.png 300w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_100,h_60,c_scale/v1613032063/W/cost-of-delay-the-vital-few/cost-of-delay-the-vital-few-100x60.png 100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 695px) 100vw, 695px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Doing that will start to show you the highly non-linear distribution of value. This doesn&#8217;t show up though until you do the slightly hard work of quantifying value and urgency.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"http://blackswanfarming.com/four-steps-to-quantifying-cost-of-delay/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1568\" height=\"1168\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_1568,h_1168/v1613032050/W/Getting-started-with-Cost-of-Delay/Getting-started-with-Cost-of-Delay.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2797\" srcset=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/v1613032050/W/Getting-started-with-Cost-of-Delay/Getting-started-with-Cost-of-Delay.png 1568w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_300,h_223,c_scale/v1613032050/W/Getting-started-with-Cost-of-Delay/Getting-started-with-Cost-of-Delay-300x223.png 300w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_768,h_572,c_scale/v1613032050/W/Getting-started-with-Cost-of-Delay/Getting-started-with-Cost-of-Delay-768x572.png 768w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_1024,h_763,c_scale/v1613032050/W/Getting-started-with-Cost-of-Delay/Getting-started-with-Cost-of-Delay-1024x763.png 1024w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_100,h_74,c_scale/v1613032050/W/Getting-started-with-Cost-of-Delay/Getting-started-with-Cost-of-Delay-100x74.png 100w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_1170,h_872,c_scale/v1613032050/W/Getting-started-with-Cost-of-Delay/Getting-started-with-Cost-of-Delay-1170x872.png 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1568px) 100vw, 1568px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Don&#8217;t stop there though. To get to a suggested order for your options you&#8217;re going to need to divide by the blocking time = &#8220;Duration&#8221;. That give you CD3. <a href=\"http://blackswanfarming.com/cost-of-delay-and-cd3-prioritisation-at-scale/\">Here&#8217;s how that works at scale</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>CD3 = <span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">C</span>ost of <span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">D</span>elay <span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">D</span>ivided by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">D</span>uration</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Hopefully that helps!</p>\n","title":"How is Cost of Delay in SAFe calculated?","date":"March 15, 2020","featuredImage":{"node":{"altText":"","localFile":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20width='400'%20height='215'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20215'%20preserveAspectRatio='none'%3e%3cpath%20d='M246%2049l-137%2066c-4%203-5%209-4%2013l22%2045c2%203%207%205%2010%205s141-65%20144-68c4-3%205-8%204-12l-22-46c-4-5-10-6-17-3m-63%2036c-38%2017-70%2033-71%2034-4%203-2%207%208%2029%2010%2023%2011%2024%2015%2025%203%200%20140-63%20143-67l2-5c0-3-19-45-21-47-5-3-6-3-76%2031m61-16l-3%202%2013%2021-3-12-4-12-3%201m-13%206l-6%204%2013%2029%2014-7-1-2c-1-2-1-2-4-1-4%202-4%203-6-2l-2-4%202-1c3-1%204-3%202-5h-3c-3%201-3%201-4-2-3-4-2-5%201-6s3-1%202-4-1-3-8%201m-16%208l-6%203%207%2015c6%2014%207%2014%209%2013%204-1%205-2%202-8-4-6-4-7-1-8s3-2%